<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,294,753]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,347,474,500]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Morphology</emphasis>
. Small bivalve. Rounded triangular shell with prominent umbos. Typical dimensions of the shell are length 
<quantity box="[271,380,510,537]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" metricValueMax="1.1" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="10.0" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="9.0">9–11 mm</quantity>
, height 7–9.5 mm, and depth 
<quantity box="[717,813,510,537]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="5.0">5–7 mm</quantity>
. For more details see 
<bibRefCitation author="Welter-Schultes, F. W." box="[1060,1357,510,537]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" refId="ref60074" refString="Welter-Schultes, F. W. (2012) European non-marine molluscs, a guide for species identification, planet poster editions. Planet Poster Editions, Gottingen, 674 pp. [in German]" type="book" year="2012">Welter-Schultes (2012: 25</bibRefCitation>
, figure at the bottom of the page).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="36" pageNumber="37" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,294,753]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,492,582,608]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Distribution and ecology</emphasis>
. Western Palearctic species found in large lowland rivers (rarely lakes) of central and eastern Europe, rarely found in western Europe. It prefers coarse sandy substrate (
<bibRefCitation author="Van Damme, D. &amp; Killeen, I. &amp; von Proschwitz, T." box="[1055,1318,618,645]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="738887" refId="ref58949" refString="Van Damme, D., Killeen, I. &amp; von Proschwitz, T. (2012) Sphaerium solidum. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species, 2012, e. T 155986 A 738887. [downloaded 15 March 2021] https: // doi. org / 10.2305 / IUCN. UK. 2012 - 1. RLTS. T 155986 A 738887. en" type="journal article" year="2012">
van Damme 
<emphasis box="[1197,1252,618,644]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[1365,1437,618,644]" name="Serbia" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Serbia</collectingCountry>
it was found in the Danube and Sava Rivers.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="36.[151,1437,294,753]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,379,690,716]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Other remarks</emphasis>
. This species is on the IUCN list of threatened species as NT (
<bibRefCitation author="Van Damme, D. &amp; Killeen, I. &amp; von Proschwitz, T." box="[1092,1368,690,717]" pageId="36" pageNumber="37" pagination="738887" refId="ref58949" refString="Van Damme, D., Killeen, I. &amp; von Proschwitz, T. (2012) Sphaerium solidum. The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species, 2012, e. T 155986 A 738887. [downloaded 15 March 2021] https: // doi. org / 10.2305 / IUCN. UK. 2012 - 1. RLTS. T 155986 A 738887. en" type="journal article" year="2012">
<collectingRegion box="[1092,1138,690,716]" country="Turkey" name="Van" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">Van</collectingRegion>
Damme 
<emphasis box="[1242,1299,690,716]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">et al.</emphasis>
2012
</bibRefCitation>
). Two nominal species are known as synonyms. On the IUCN Red List it has been assessed as NT (Killeen 
<emphasis box="[1282,1331,726,752]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">et al</emphasis>
. 2011 
<emphasis box="[1400,1412,727,752]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="37">c</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
